CNCP v1 23022
{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#5975: Add support for AbortController to renderToString and Streaming APIs",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:26:13.692003+00:00",
  "text": "Add support for AbortController to renderToString and Streaming APIs\n\n### What problem does this feature solve?\r\n\r\nRight now if you abort a request while a server is still rendering your app it won't stop until the whole app is rendered.\r\nThis leads to unnecessary workload for aborted requests (for example multiple page refreshes).\r\n\r\n### What does the proposed API look like?\r\n\r\n`renderToString` and Streaming APIs should be able to receive a `signal` from [`AbortController`](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/AbortController) and stop execution if controller was aborted.\r\n\r\n```js\r\nconst controller = new AbortController()\r\n\r\nconst resultPromise = renderToString(App, ssrContext, controller.signal)\r\n\r\nrequest.on('close', () => { controller.abort() })\r\n\r\nresultPromise\r\n  .then((result) => {\r\n    request.send(result)\r\n  })\r\n  .catch((error) => {\r\n    if (error instanceof AbortError) { ... } // type of error is to be discussed\r\n    else { ... }\r\n  })\r\n```",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    ":sparkles: feature request",
    "scope: ssr"
  ],
